Class EfsDispatcherThread.AgentStats

java.lang.Object
org.efs.dispatcher.EfsDispatcherThread.AgentStats
Enclosing class:
EfsDispatcherThread
public final class EfsDispatcherThread.AgentStats extends Object
This class is used to track agent performance for a variety of statistics: time spent on dispatcher ready queue, time spent processing events, and number of event processed per run. These statistics are on a per dispatcher thread basis.

Note: the data stored in an AgentStats instance is "live" which means that the performance data is update by the dispatcher thread over time. It is recommended that an application routinely monitor dispatcher these statistics over time to detect dispatcher performance degradation.

Author:
Charles W. Rapp
